
#1. Data Sources & APIs
#Source	Type	Notes / Example Integration
SentimenTA (morritse)	Stocks	Free API for sentiment on stocks from Reddit/Twitter
Alpaca API	Stock trading	Paper trading + real trading endpoints for automation
Inverse r/CryptoCurrency Bot	Reddit NLP	Provides crypto sentiment with VADER; negative = contrarian buy signal
SwaggyStocks / QuiverQuant	Retail sentiment + options flow	Can be scraped or use their APIs
Reddit API + Pushshift	Social data	Pull trending tickers, posts, karma, and sentiment
Refinitiv / LSEG	Institutional sentiment feed	(Paid feed) used by hedge funds for sentiment data
VanEck BUZZ & MEME ETFs	Benchmark data	Compare your composite sentiment score to ETF holdings
DIY NLP	Your own VADER or FinBERT layer	Evaluate post or tweet tone
Exchange APIs (Binance, Coinbase, Alpaca)	Execution layer	For both crypto & equities
